  m_Name: Forepaw_Digit3_Middle_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Forepaw_Digit3_Middle_L
  partName: Forepaw Digit3 Middle Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left forepaw digit three middle phalanx forms the central segment of the
    third toe within the canine forepaw and supports coordinated digital movement.
    Positioned between the proximal and distal phalanges, it contributes to flexibility,
    stability, and controlled weight distribution during locomotion.
  - Tendons and ligaments attached to this bone enable smooth toe flexion and extension
    necessary for balanced movement and traction. The third digit plays a major role
    in supporting body weight and maintaining stable paw contact with the ground.
